text:
Summary by Egyptian Gazette ABU DHABI – Al-Ahly clinched the 2023 Egyptian Super Cup for the 14th time after defeating Modern Future 4-2 victory in the final played at Mohammed Bin Zayed Stadium in Abu Dhabi. Striker Mahmoud Abdel-Moneim ‘Kahraba’ and winger Hussein el-Shahat grabbed first-half goals in the 13th and 35th minutes respectively to hand the African champions a two-goal lead, but coach Marcel Koller’s side was rattled after South African winger Percy Tau was su… Share menu More
